english:
  title: On the Cloud and Moon Pavilion at High Peak
  author: Kim Su-on
  language: eng
  text: |-
    I have long dismissed such doctrines,
    so how could I speak by borrowing their words?
    Yet Maeja of Yeongnam has honored me with friendship these many years,
    and now asks me to inscribe the Cloud and Moon Pavilion—
    a request whose purpose I cannot abandon.

    Though some might fault me for a child playing sage beyond his years,
    I offer this reflection:

    Clouds rise and fall, the moon waxes and wanes—
    yet neither matches the clarity of the empty sky itself.
    So I speak to you, O recluse of the heights:
    do not spend your life toying with shadow and light.
  footnotes:
    - The 'Cloud and Moon Pavilion' (운월헌) is a retreat associated with spiritual cultivation and retreat from worldly affairs. The poet's inscription plays on this symbolism.
    - The reference to 'Maeja of Yeongnam' suggests a respected scholar-friend whose request compels the author to set aside his usual philosophical reservations and offer this teaching.
